hamshire, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Thany","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Fritz, Klaus.","English and Scottish: variant of   Thain  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thain","meanings":["Scottish (Aberdeenshire and Banffshire) and English (East Anglia): status name from Middle English and Older Scots <i>thein</i>, <i>theyn</i> ‘thane’ (Old English and Old Norse <i>thegn</i>), for a person of high social rank, a noble retainer, a warrior, or a senior government officer. Compare   Knight  . In Scotland in the later Middle Ages the term was used to denote someone who held land directly from the king. Sometimes also from the Old Norse personal name <i>Thegn</i>, derived from the same word."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Thany was born in 1207, in Stanwell, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom. She married John Drokenford in 1251, in Buckinghamshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1207–":"1207–Surnud","1195–Male":"1195–Surnud","1221–Male":"1221–Surnud","1253–1300":"1253–1300","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1300":"1300","1221":"1221","1253":"1253","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","1207":"1207","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bradenlove, Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1207–":"1207–Kuollut","1195–Male":"1195–Kuollut","1221–Male":"1221–Kuollut","1253–1300":"1253–1300","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1221":"1221","1253":"1253","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","1207":"1207","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bradenlove, Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1207–":"1207–Décédée","1195–Male":"1195–Décédé","1221–Male":"1221–Décédé","1253–1300":"1253–1300","1207–Female":"1207–Décédée","1300":"1300","1221":"1221","1253":"1253","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","1207":"1207","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bradenlove, Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","B